# afrobarometer_variables (done)

Metadata about Afrobarometer rounds, primarily the names of variables.

- round
- country
- withinwt
- combinwt
- respondent
- respondent_other
- respondent
- respondent_other
- interview
- interview_other
- interviewer
- interviewer_other


# language_variables (done)

- round: Afrobarometer round number. integer. 1--6.
- variable: string. Variable name in Afrobarometer
- type: string. Variable type
- other: boolean. Whether this variable has the literal responses for the "Other".

# countries

Afrobarometer countries in each round

- round: Afrobarometer round number. integer. 1--6.
- value: Value of the country variable
- label: Label of the country variable
- iso_alpha2: ISO 3166 Alpha-2 code for the country.

# language_names

Matches names to variables

- name: character. All lower case (but non-ASCII unicode characters allowed) version
    name.
- country: character. ISO 3166 Alpha-2
- Glottolog: space sep list of Glottolog codes
- ISO 639-3: space sep list of ISO 639-3 codes
- WALS: space sep list of WALS codes


# language_country

Afrobarometer languages in each round

- round: Afrobarometer round number. integer. 1--6.
- value: Value of the language variable
- label: Label of the language variable.
- lang_name: Name used to match with values in this dataset.
- n: number of observations
- withinwt: weighted number observations within the country


# langauge_respno

Afrobarometer language by respondent.

- round
- respno
- variable
- lang_name
- lang_name

# language dists

Distances between survey language values.




## Notes

- ISO 639-3
  - non-missing (use und/mis, etc. codes)
  - all missing values are accounted for
  - one macrolanguage only
  - country usage
- Glottolog
  - only one match
  - whitelist family entries
  - country usage
  - only missing if ISO 639-3 is
  - African macroarea
- WALS
  - all in same genus
  - country usage
  - only missing if ISO 639-3 is
  - African macroarea
